6.7.24  9:23 am   I've been working on a project for the past couple of months, and things have been going very well. I'm not running into any big issues, and the things that I am creating are looking and feeling great. I just finished a big chunk of work on the project (that took a lot longer than expected), and I'm moving onto the next part that needs working, and I just can't do it. I'm looking at the computer, telling myself that I need to get started, and I can't seem to bring myself to do it. This is something that I've experienced before, but this is the first time I've caught myself so early in the process. It sucks too, because I'm scared of losing the projects potential, but I can't seem to get myself to fulfill it. Any tips? Maybe I just need to *quit being a baby* and grab hunker down over some coffee...

      i think it's time to briefly describe and summarize what you've done on the project, and why you started it. which will lead you to a brief description and summary of what you think you ought to do next, and why. compare your original plan to what you think the plan ought to be now. just to make sure you are on the same page as yourself
